@Api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5204

### ─── BOOTSTRAP: Seed or create tenant first ─────────────────
### Option A: dotnet run --project src/Api -- --seed
###   → creates tenant "acme" + admin user (admin@mtsp.dev / Admin123!)
### Option B: POST /api/tenants first, then register below
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register a new user (tenant must already exist)
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@mtsp.dev",
  "password": "Passw0rd!",
  "displayName": "Test User",
  "tenantSlug": "acme"
}

### Login → copy accessToken, set @Token below
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@mtsp.dev",
  "password": "Passw0rd!"
}

### Refresh token (reads refresh_token cookie)
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/refresh

### ─── Authenticated requests ─────────────────────────────────
@Token =

### Get current user profile
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}

### Update profile
PATCH {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "displayName": "Jane Doe"
}

### Update profile (email)
PATCH {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@mtsp.dev"
}

### Delete current user (soft-delete)
DELETE {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}

### List tenant users (admin)
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}
